=== Tangible Cultural Properties designated by Takarazuka City ===
[[File:Mefu-jinja (Takarazuka), sekihi.jpg|thumb|220px|right|{{center|Shrine name stone marker}}]]
* Mefu Shrine name stone marker (with: two documents) (archaeological materials) – Erected in the first year of {{ill|lt=Genbun|Q1145754|WD=Q1145754|1=Genbun}} ({{ill|lt=1736|Q6989|WD=Q6989|1=1736}}). The accompanying designation includes the original and a copy of “Memo on the Stone Monument of Mefu Shrine.” Designated on March 30, {{ill|lt=1976|Q2480|WD=Q2480|1=1976}} ({{ill|lt=Shōwa|Q327567|WD=Q327567|1=Shōwa era}} 51).<ref name="Takarazuka Cultural Properties">[http://www.city.takarazuka.hyogo.jp/kyoiku/rekishi/1003729.html Cultural Properties of Takarazuka] (Takarazuka City website).</ref>

=== Natural Monuments designated by Takarazuka City ===
* Mefu Shrine grove – Designated on March 30, 1976 (Shōwa 51).<ref name="Takarazuka Cultural Properties"/>

=== Annual festival ===
The {{ill|lt=Danjiri Festival|Q5219928|WD=Q5219928|1=Danjiri Matsuri}} held on October 18 and 19 is co-hosted with {{ill|lt=Yasaka Shrine (Kiyoshikōjin, Takarazuka)|UNKNOWN|lt=Yasaka Shrine}} ({{ill|lt=Takarazuka City|Q823967|WD=Q823967|1=Takarazuka, Hyōgo}}{{ill|lt=Kiyoshikōjin (Takarazuka)|UNKNOWN|lt=Kiyoshikōjin}}), during which two {{ill|lt=festival floats|Q11424706|WD=Q11424706|1=danjiri}}—one from Kometani East (Mefu, Kometani) and one from Kometani West (Kiyoshikōjin)—enter the shrine precincts.

=== Location and access ===
* 1-1 Mefu Yamate-chō, Takarazuka City, Hyōgo Prefecture
* 5-minute walk from {{ill|lt=Mefu Shrine Station|Q6807953|WD=Q6807953|1=Mefu-Jinja Station}} on the {{ill|lt=Hankyu Takarazuka Main Line|Q3832859|WD=Q3832859|1=Hankyu Takarazuka Main Line}}

